==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Romanize
<hw>Ro"man*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Romanized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Romanizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To Latinize; to fill with Latin words or idioms.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To convert to the Roman Catholic religion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Romanize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Romanize
<hw>Ro"man*ize</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To use Latin
words and idioms.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Apishly <xex>Romanizing</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To conform to Roman Catholic opinions, customs, or
modes of speech.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Romanizer</ent>⟦br⟧
